<paragraph id="8BA3D655A61B0604FF46FCF9FC8AE7E4" blockId="46.[188,1399,848,982]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<bibRefCitation id="EF8DABA4A61B0604FF46FCF9FE45E75B" author="Zhang Y. - W. &amp; Li Y. - G." box="[189,423,848,874]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="767 - 779" refId="ref46138" refString="Zhang Y. - W. &amp; Li Y. - G. 1997. Coleoptera: Glaphyridae, Dynastidae and Melolonthidae. In: Yang X. - K. (ed.) Insect of the three Gorge Reservoir Area of Yangtze River: 767 - 779. Chongqing Publishers, Chongqing." type="book chapter" year="1997">Zhang &amp; Li (1997)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C1CADD6A61B0604FDD7FCF9FCE5E75B" box="[556,775,848,874]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Holotrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wangi">
<emphasis id="B9680A47A61B0604FDD7FCF9FCE5E75B" box="[556,775,848,874]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Holotrichia wangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a male specimen from 
<collectingRegion id="49D818B7A61B0604FB64FCF9FB1CE75B" box="[1183,1278,848,874]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry id="F30B96C5A61B0604FAD2FCF9FA91E75B" box="[1321,1395,848,874]" name="China" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">China</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8DABA4A61B0604FF46FCDDFE88E7BE" author="Bezdek A." box="[189,362,884,911]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" pagination="249 - 280" refId="ref43171" refString="Bezdek A. 2016. Tribe Rhizotrogini Burmeister, 1855. In: Lobl I. &amp; Lobl D. (eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 3. Scarabaeoidea - Scirtoidea - Dascilloidea - Buprestoidea - Byrrhoidea. Revised and updated edition: 249 - 280. Koninklijke Brill NV, Leiden, The Netherlands." type="book chapter" year="2016">Bezděk (2016)</bibRefCitation>
transferred this species to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1CADD6A61B0604FD5BFCDDFCEAE7BF" baseAuthorityName="Nomura" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[672,776,884,910]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Miridiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9680A47A61B0604FD5BFCDDFCEAE7BF" box="[672,776,884,910]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Miridiba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We have studied the 
<typeStatus id="54A768F7A61B0604FBFCFCDDFB93E7BF" box="[1031,1137,884,910]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">holotype</typeStatus>
, which shows features of external morphology and male genitalia characteristic of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1CADD6A61B0604FC80FC31FC01E783" baseAuthorityName="Nomura" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[891,995,920,946]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Miridiba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9680A47A61B0604FC80FC31FC01E783" box="[891,995,920,946]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Miridiba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and morphotype I “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C1CADD6A61B0604FB34FC31FA80E783" box="[1231,1378,920,946]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Trichophora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9680A47A61B0604FB34FC31FA80E783" box="[1231,1378,920,946]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Trichophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”. Hence, this species is included in this genital morphotype.
</paragraph>
